  "text": "Comparison to State-of-the-art Systems Table 4 summarizes the performance of our model and the best published results for the SPMRL and the CTB5 datasets. 11 On both datasets, our system outperforms the baselines. On the SPMRL 2013 shared task, our approach yields a 2.1% TedEval score gain over the top performing system [CITATION_1] . We also improve the segmentation and dependency F-scores by 3.1% and 4.8% respectively. Note that the POS F-scores are not directly comparable because [CITATION_2] use a different POS tagset from us. On the CTB5 dataset, we outperform the state-of-the-art with respect to all The normalized score of the output tree as the function of the number of restarts. We normalize scores of each sentence by the highest score among 3,000 restarts for this sentence. We show the curve up to 1,000 restarts because it reaches convergence after 500 restarts.",
